<p>Ann Arbor's cold climate demands robust HVAC systems capable of handling winter temperatures that frequently drop below freezing. For heating, high-efficiency natural gas furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher are most popular, though cold-climate heat pumps are gaining traction as technology improves. Modern cold-climate heat pumps can effectively heat homes down to -5¬∞F, making them viable for Ann Arbor's winters while providing excellent cooling efficiency during hot, humid summers.</p>

